dict.string: The information Siri uses to respond to your requests will be removed from Apple servers. If you want to use Siri later, it will take time to re-send this information.
Siri sends information like your voice input, contacts, and location to Apple to process your requests.
Siri helps you get things done just by asking. You can make a phone call, send a message, dictate a note, or even find a restaurant. About Siri and Privacy…
